Now I have the complete picture. I can see the full structure. The `contentArea` uses `overflow-x: auto` at narrow widths but the Nav is a sibling (outside `.contentArea`), so it IS expected to stay fluid. Let me now make both fixes:

**Fix 1: `Navigation.module.scss`** — The CSS looks mostly correct but has a gap. `.logo` has `flex-shrink: 0` and `.logoText` has `white-space: nowrap`, but there's no `white-space: nowrap` on the `.logo` element itself (the `inline-flex` link), and critically `.navInner` has no `flex-wrap: nowrap` to prevent any multi-line wrapping of the row. Also, the `.logo` gap uses `$portfolio-spacer-0-5x` (a SCSS variable without `var()`), which should be verified — but the more pressing structural issue is that the logo + the mark together inside the `inline-flex` need to be fully protected.

**Fix 2: `docs/design-anti-patterns.md`** — AP-066 needs to be updated to formally codify the Identity Tier Priority rule the user is describing.

**Fix 3: `docs/design/branding.md`** — Add the identity tier priority rule as a canonical section.

Here are all the changes:

---

### **Fix 1 — `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`**

The `.navInner` needs `flex-wrap: nowrap` (belt) to guarantee the row never breaks. The `.logo` element needs `white-space: nowrap` at the container level (suspenders) so the browser can never flow it internally. And we should document the yield contract right in the SCSS.

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  // ── IDENTITY TIER PRIORITY (AP-066) ────────────────────────────────────
  // The nav bar is always one row. `nowrap` is the outer guarantee that the
  // logo + links never stack, regardless of viewport width. The logo itself
  // carries `flex-shrink: 0` + `white-space: nowrap` (inner guarantee).
  // The tagline is the designated yield point — it absorbs squeeze by
  // wrapping onto a second line (up to 2 lines, via -webkit-line-clamp).
  // The logo NEVER yields. The tagline ALWAYS yields first. This is a
  // portfolio identity rule, not a layout preference.
  flex-wrap: nowrap;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  // ── IDENTITY TIER: RIGID (AP-066) ──────────────────────────────────────
  // The logo is Tier 1 identity — it MUST render on one line at all viewport
  // widths. Three properties working together:
  //   flex-shrink: 0  → flex container cannot compress this item
  //   white-space: nowrap → the inline-flex link element itself cannot wrap
  //   min-width: max-content → prevents any implicit size calculation from
  //     allowing the browser to allocate less space than the content needs
  // All three are required. Removing any one creates a vector for wrapping
  // under extreme squeeze.
  flex-shrink: 0;
  white-space: nowrap;
  min-width: max-content;
  text-decoration: none;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  // ── IDENTITY TIER: YIELD POINT (AP-066) ────────────────────────────────
  // This side is the designated absorber. When the viewport is squeezed,
  // the links column shrinks via min-width: 0. The tagline child is allowed
  // to wrap (up to 2 lines). Nav links (when present) are never expected to
  // wrap — they are short labels. Only the tagline wraps.
  min-width: 0;
  // Align items to the top when tagline wraps to 2 lines, so the logo mark
  // and first line of tagline sit at the same optical baseline.
  align-items: flex-start;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  // ── IDENTITY TIER: DESIGNATED YIELD (AP-066) ───────────────────────────
  // The tagline is Tier 2 — it CAN wrap. It is the soft edge of the nav.
  // At narrow viewports it compresses onto up to 2 lines. It never pushes
  // the logo or causes the nav to grow taller than 2 lines of tagline text.
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

Key changes from the current file:
1. **`flex-wrap: nowrap`** added to `.navInner` — the outer belt
2. **`white-space: nowrap`** + **`min-width: max-content`** added to `.logo` — the inner suspenders (these are in addition to `flex-shrink: 0` which was already there)
3. **`align-items: flex-start`** on `.links` — so when the tagline wraps to 2 lines, the first line stays optically aligned to the logo, not the flex row center
4. **`white-space: nowrap`** added to `.link` — nav links themselves should also never wrap (they're short labels)
5. All three guarantee comments updated to describe the full triple-lock on `.logo`

