### **Fix 2 — `docs/design-anti-patterns.md`**

AP-066 exists but doesn't formally name the **Identity Tier Priority** rule. Update it to codify this as a named, referenceable principle. Find the existing AP-066 entry and replace it:

**Locate:** The `## AP-066` section in `docs/design-anti-patterns.md`

**Current entry** (reconstruct from what we know — it's in the Navigation & Menus category, referencing FB-146).

**Replace with:**

```markdown
<a id="ap-066"></a>
## AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text

**Status: ACTIVE**

**Category:** Navigation & Menus

**Trigger:** A flex nav bar where the logo or site name can wrap to two lines under viewport squeeze, because the logo element lacks the full triple-lock (`flex-shrink: 0` + `white-space: nowrap` + `min-width: max-content`) or the outer flex row lacks `flex-wrap: nowrap`.

**Why it's wrong:** The logo / site name is a Tier 1 identity element. It is the reader's orientation anchor — the signal that says "this is where you are." If it wraps to two lines, the nav becomes taller, the layout shifts, and the site reads as broken. There is no viewport width at which this is acceptable. This is not a layout preference — it is a portfolio identity rule on the same level as zero border-radius.

**Identity Tier Priority — canonical rule:**

> **Tier 1 (Rigid):** Logo mark + site name (`Yilan Gao`). NEVER wraps. NEVER shrinks. Non-negotiable at any viewport width.
>
> **Tier 2 (Yield):** The tagline / role blurb (`Designer, AI systems experience…`). CAN wrap to a maximum of 2 lines. This is the designated absorber for viewport squeeze. It yields so Tier 1 doesn't have to.
>
> **Tier 3 (Optional):** Nav links. Present only when populated. Short labels; should not wrap, but are secondary to both Tier 1 and Tier 2 in priority ordering.

Any future nav work must preserve this hierarchy. The tagline yields. The logo never does.

**Correct alternative — triple-lock on the logo:**
```scss
.logo {
  flex-shrink: 0;        // flex container cannot compress this item
  white-space: nowrap;   // inline-flex element itself cannot wrap
  min-width: max-content; // no implicit size calculation can under-allocate space
}

.navInner {
  flex-wrap: nowrap;     // outer guarantee: the row never becomes two rows
}

.links {
  min-width: 0;          // designated yield side — can shrink to nothing
}

.tagline {
  min-width: 0;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2; // max 2 lines — absorbs squeeze, never grows further
  overflow: hidden;
}
```

All four declarations are required together. Removing any one creates a compression vector.

**See:** FB-146 (nav logo wrapping), FB-150 (company names in experience column — same tier principle applied to tabular data).
```

